jobtitle: You will get WordPress running on AWS with Autoscaling + High Availability
talent_desc:
You will get a high-availability WordPress infrastructure hosted on AWS, using the following services:

- Elastic Beanstalk: to manage the compute layer (web/app servers)
- RDS: to manage the database layer
- CloudFront: to serve as a CDN in front of the app
- S3: to store the media uploads
- SES: to deliver the email messages sent from the contact forms
- CodePipeline: to handle automatic CI/CD deployments from GitHub or CodeCommit repositories

This configuration provides the best possible performance for non-persistent WordPress high availability environments. Configurations based on EFS network file systems have very poor performance, since running PHP files on network drives is very inefficient.
In this case, we will use EBS volumes to host the web instances, which provide the best latency and access time.

This infrastructure is intended so that WordPress site updates (core, themes, or plugins updates) are performed through a GIT repository (GitHub, CodeCommit, BitBucket) instead of doing it from the backend web interface (wp-admin).

jobtitle: You will get Report for Vulnerability Assessment and Penetration Testing of Web App
talent_desc:
The best way to find flaws in your web application is by doing penetration testing, also known as Pen Test or Pen Testing. This is the most widely used security testing strategy for most web applications.

Web application penetration testing is carried out by initiating simulated attacks, both internally and externally, to get access to sensitive data.
Web penetration testing allows the end-user to determine any security weakness of the entire web application and across its components, including the source code, database, and back-end network). This helps the developer in prioritizing the pinpointed vulnerabilities and threats, and come up with strategies to mitigate them
In a nutshell, web penetration testing is a preventive control measure that lets you analyze the overall status of the existing security layer of a system. 
These are the common goals of doing pen testing for web apps:
Identify unknown vulnerabilities
Check the effectiveness of the existing security policies
Test publicly exposed components, including firewalls, routers, and DNS
Determine the most vulnerable route for an attack
Look for loopholes that could lead to the data theft

Fingerprint the installed WordPress version
Show the vulnerabilities for the running WordPress version
Enumerate the installed plugins and their versions
Show the vulnerabilities for the identified plugins
Enumerate the installed themes and their versions
Show the vulnerabilities for the identified themes
Enumerate the WordPress users

The next step is to fingerprint the running versions of those components and to search for public vulnerabilities affecting them. A lot of public exploits are also available online.

These hacks can be prevented by periodically scanning and identifying vulnerable components. Order your EZPZ WordPress scan today and be safe!

jobtitle: You will get CI/CD pipelines using Azure DevOps
talent_desc:
Working on large projects, I have seen the horror that goes on in CI/CD. There's a lot of manual work that needs to be done to build and deploy applications in the cloud. A lot of arcane knowledge that you had to have in order to work effectively with the CI/CD part. A lot of dependencies between CI/CDs that if you made changes to one of them, you had to restore the work on the other ones.

I came to the conclusion that the CI/CD part should be easy to use, that there is less manual work, that there are no dependencies between different pipelines, that's what you get if you use my services.

I will set you up a full cycle of CI/CD for your applications. I use Azure Pipelines for CI and CD parts I don't use Azure Release pipelines as they can introduce confusing processes. By best practice I use Azure pipelines templates to build pipelines. This means that the final pipeline consists of templates that are responsible for only one of their jobs (Single-responsibility principle) and they can be reused in other pipelines.

jobtitle: You will get more reliable delivery of your emails to your recipients' inboxes
talent_desc:
Are you worried about your email deliverability? Are your emails always being filtered as spam?  Are you worried that your recipients are not responding to your emails? Do you consider email deliverability an issue only for bulk mails?

The landscape has changed.  The time when a SPF record was all you needed to ensure your emails reached your recipients' inboxes has gone and the standard for even basic deliverability has increased such that you need to keep up or your emails will forever be a victim of spam filters.

The first step in resolving your deliverability issues is knowing why your emails are either not being delivered or not being delivered into your recipients' inboxes.  As an experienced deliverability consultant I can help you understand why your deliverability is lower than you expect, explain the steps needed to improve your deliverability and also action those steps. Once we've done all we can to improve your deliverability and you still have issues with certain providers, such as Google, Microsoft, then I can look deeper and check domain/IP address reputation and blacklists.

By the end of the project you will see an improvement in email deliverability.

jobtitle: You will get postfix secure email server with webmail client like rainloop, roundcube.
talent_desc:
Postfix is one of the most widely used and easiest mail server solutions available. It is a free, open-source, and powerful Mail Transfer Agent (MTA) that can be used to send and receive email.  By default, Postfix is the default MTA software on all Linux distributions.

Dovecot is an open-source IMAP and POP3 email server that can act as a mail storage server. It is used to deliver and retrieve emails to and from local mailboxes.

Roundcube is a web-based IMAP email client that can read emails stored by Dovecot on virtual mailboxes. It provides all features you expect from an email client including MIME support, multiple sender identities, spell checking, folder manipulation, and many more.

In this project I will set up a full-featured Mail server with Postfix, Dovecot and Roundcube and spamassassin.

- Then I conduct a Penetration Test on the infrastructure (web application, mobile application, network, etc) and create a technical report with an executive summary of my findings.

jobtitle: You will get etl queries jobs and packages using ssis
talent_desc:
The ‘T’ is ETL stands for transformation. The goal of transformation is to convert raw input data to an PowerBI Data Visualization. This is also known as dimensional modelling. Understanding dimensional modelling is essential for building BI systems.



An ETL process is a program that periodically runs on a server and orchestrates the refresh of the data in the BI system. SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) is a development tool and runtime that is optimized for building ETL processes. SSIS lets you design ETL processes in a graphical way (but if needed you can write parts using VB or C#). The SSIS components are highly optimized for ETL type tasks and the SSIS run-time executes independent tasks in parallel where possible.

I perform fuzzy data matching, record linkage, merging, de-duplication and cleansing of datasets and spreadsheets. Availability of a reliable master data for a supply chain can be crucial for success of a company. Supply chain performance is dependent on consistent definitions of customers, products, items, locations, and other master data objects. When data is poorly governed and inconsistent, supply chain become less competitive. Good data leads to efficient supply chains, allowing resources to be spent on innovation rather than on coping with problems. However, business data is often messy, containing duplicate entries of same entities, missing information, having misspellings and various other errors. In many cases, there is no unique identifier which can be used to unambiguously identify an entity. When such data sources need to be linked or de-duplicated solely based on string similarity, it is called fuzzy data matching.

jobtitle: You will get real duration of overlapped events. (Data enrichment about time assignment)
talent_desc:
Many times, events are first designed for a period of time but updated before their end (for instance, a new price or health treatment): lower price to foster sales, higher price before stockout, new treatment that may replace or not the precedent one.

With the correct duration, predictions of units sold based on price (by the event) are more accurate. In health, if a medicine or physical therapy is affected by another medicine or by a new condition of the patient, its performance is better estimated with the real duration: for instance, if a patient is unable to collaborate doing gymnastics due to new conditions or medicines, the original “gymnastics” event lasted (=duration) less days. 

Starter is for up to 100,000 events (=rows in a worksheet) (No maximum number of events by ID). Standard is for up to 1 million events in a sheet (approaching Excel limit). Advanced is for over 1 million.

In Starter and Standard tiers, only days are considered: Duration is an integer number.
In Advanced, if you wish, hours and minutes are considered: Duration may have decimals.

Attached PDFs to understand how Duration is computed in Starter and Standard tiers. Advanced is a customized version.

jobtitle: You will get accurate weekly P&L report for B2C retailers in ecommerce
talent_desc:
This project is for B2C online retailers who are generating thousands of dollar sales weekly but experience tight cash flow. The goal of this project is to calculate how profitable you are for the week. Yes weekly, so that you can immediately close promotions and downsells/upsells that are not profitable or double up on those that are adding most to your bottom line. 
Shopping cart or amazon's statistics/P&L dashboard is sometimes misleading for it does not show real time adjustments such as refunds, cancellations, or pending sales. I've often seen sellers who get very disappointed to see less money coming in their bank, not even close to the dollar sales they see in their shopping cart dashboards. The dashboard's use really (this is coming from a popular shopping cart provider) is to show you a snapshot of your day's sales, whether all of those sales eventually materialize to dollars is a different matter. To get the real numbers you need to get the transaction dump, that needs to be cleaned up and organized before it makes sense. Here's where I come in, I will clean up and analyze these data dump and create the real picture of your sales for the week and send it to you 1-2 days.

What is Web Scraping?

Web Scraping is a process to scrape website data by using automation as there are many programming languages like python, PHP, javascript, Visual Basic For Application (VBA). A developer writes the script in the backend and performs the front-end task to get the data from the web.

How web scraping help to make the process fast?

There are many manual processes where the end-user gets the data from the website and collects it in Excel for data analysis. Either a user does it manually or make it automate, but a non-technical person can't make the process automate. On the other hand, a developer creates a script and uses their skills to automate the process so that an end-user uses the script many times that will help to increase work efficiency and faster as compared to manual work.

talent_desc:
I try to focus on a very particular type of task:
- You need data from a website downloaded in data format file/s (CSV, XLSX, etc).

It is hard to anticipate complexity before I get your specs, but generally I would categorize jobs in:
- 1-2 days delivery: The website has under 20k pages and good speed. Steps to obtain the data are basic (no click on a tab and wait for a spinner, etc).
- 1 week delivery: Up to 100k pages. Total HTML to download ranges up to 3-10 GB. Website structure can be more complicated (multiple listing page formats, clicking some tabs to get data, etc).
- 2 weeks delivery: Up to 500k pages, HTML up to 10-30GB in total.

But it is not the purpose that you know upfront which of the 3 categories to choose. In some cases I may crawl up to 1 mil pages at the price of 100k pages. In other (rare) cases the data can not be scraped or can cost even more.

jobtitle: You will get 3-Tier Auto-Scalable Web Application Architecture
talent_desc:
What is solving?
Modularity: 
The essence of having a three-tier architecture is to modularize our application such that each part can be managed independently of the other. 
Scalability: 
Each tier of the architecture can scale horizontally to support the traffic and request demand coming to it. This can easily be done by adding more EC2 instances to each tier and load balancing across them. 

High Availability: 
With Cloud, I can design the infrastructure to be highly available by hosting our application in different locations known as the availability zones.

Fault-Tolerant: 
I want the infrastructure to comfortably adapt to any unexpected change both to traffic and fault. This is usually done by adding a redundant system that will account for such a hike in traffic when it does occur. 

Security: 
Design an infrastructure that is highly secured As much as possible, to avoid exposing interactions within the application over the internet. This simply means that the application will communicate within themselves with a private IP.

jobtitle: You will get Create a Sandwich Bot, Mempool Sandwich bot for Pancakeswap, ETH Sandwich
talent_desc:
🏆🏆What really is a Crypto Sandwich Bot?🏆🏆

Here is the Basic explanation behind it.

⚡⚡Sandwich trading” refers to the process in which a bot is programmed by software developers to spot when another trader is trying to purchase a token or a bit of cryptocurrency on a blockchain network, like Ether or Cardano. The bot then places an order on that same token.⚡⚡

🏆⚡What is a Sandwich attack? A victim transaction trades a crypto-currency asset X (ex: ETH, DAI, SAI, VERI) to another crypto-asset Y and makes a large purchase. A bot sniffs out the transaction and Front-Runs the victim by purchasing asset Y before the large trade is approved.⚡🏆

⚡🏆A sandwich attack Bot Operates by  "sandwiching" the Target’s transactions between two transactions initiated by the Searcher or Attacker, which Reorders transactions and benefits the Attacker.🏆⚡

jobtitle: You will get a code review and recommendations on further software improvements
talent_desc:
Code review is a part of the software development process which involves testing the source code to identify bugs at any development stage. 

During this process, developers usually review source code to find issues, analyze architecture quality and share recommendations. It’s crucial to have reviewers outside the key development team to guarantee the high quality and neutrality of the review. 

We’re all people, so any software may have mistakes, mistypes, security flaws, erroneous architecture, business logic issues, another restrictions. Any issue or limitation is cheaper and easier to fix at an early stage. After the release, such issues may cost you severe losses. 
Based on my experience, two of three projects we were reviewing, had problems with the code that might have serious consequences. Thanks to a well-timed review, they managed to avoid them. 

An effective code review prevents bugs and errors from getting into your project by improving code quality at an early stage of the software development process.

jobtitle: You will get an interpreter translating natural language text to code
talent_desc:
The human interface library -simply called 'hi'- is built on top of several open source components that can turn natural language text (English or Hungarian currently) to structured analyses of which all the necessary information can be extracted to translate the text to a language that can be understood by computers. The currently supported ones are javascript and shell script, though these can be used to generate yet another target like SQL. The translation process is carried out in two steps: first morphological, syntactic and semantic analyses are carried out whose results are handed over to the caller/client program in JSON structure, then the analyses need to be parsed by the client to generate a translation (or just extract information for tagging and classification). A beta demo for an Android client is available in play store as well called 'hi - Human Interface'.

jobtitle: You will get Enhanced eMail Reputation (No more emails on spam)
talent_desc:

For this service, we will perform the following for your eMail domain:

Configure DKIM - DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) is a digital signature attached to each sent message, verifying that the message originated from the sender’s domain. 

 Configure SPF - Sender Policy Framework (SPF) is an email validation system designed to prevent eMail spoofing by providing a means to verify that the messages were sent from a computer that is authorized to send messages for the domain. 

Configure rDNS - Reverse DNS allows the recipient to confirm what domain name is associated with the IP address of the computer that sent the message. A PTR record will be created in your DNS for this purpose.

Configure Sender ID - This configuration is similar to SPF, and is used by AOL and a few other large service providers.

Notes:
The one-time fee for this service is priced on a per-domain basis.

jobtitle: You will get a dockerized LEMP environment on AWS EC2 instance for wordpress
talent_desc:
Once you order an EC2 (Linux) instance from AWS, you will need to set up a stack of software that will allow you to deploy the WordPress website on that server. In most cases, developers are setting up a LAMP stack (Linux + Apache + MySQL + PHP) which is not optimal, as the Apache webserver, however Apache is to create a different threads per each request meanwhile Nginx handles multiple requests within one thread, as a result, Apache consumes more metal resource. In other words, the same machine with Nginx able to handle more requests per second on the same machine with exact same resources.

Everything I install (besides the MySQL database) is in a docker container, which allows you to easily scale or migrate your environment to another server without headaches.

What you will get as a result on your EC2 instance or Docker container

- PHP 7.4 with configured and optimized opcache and apcu
- Mysql 8 
- Nginx server with PHP-FPM on port 80 with ability to handle multiple WordPress sites
- Apache server on other port i.e. 8080
- PhpMyAdmin
- Deployed scratch WordPress website if needed.
     
    moreabout the product details

Metricbeat : Collect metrics from your systems and services. From CPU to memory, Redis to NGINX, and much more, Metricbeat is a lightweight way to send system and service statistics.

Heartbeat : 
Is your host, network device, or even your third-party service available? Check if it’s alive with a basic ICMP ping.
Is your DNS up? How about a third-party FTP server? When you need to go beyond the availability of a device, the TCP check inspects individual ports.
Is your website up? The HTTP / HTTPS check verifies that specific endpoints are up and returning the correct text and status codes.

Auditbeat : Collect your Linux audit framework data and monitor the integrity of your files. Auditbeat ships these events in real time to the rest of the Elastic Stack for further analysis.
